Rewrote the slat_recognition script

title: Rewrote the slat_recognition script
message:
Rewrote the slat_recognition script

The script calculates a rotation error in the input image and reverses the rotation.
The script implements all tested filters in single functions.

title: Removed unnecessary file
message: Removed unnecessary file

title: Four Points now added
message: Four Points now added

title: added new filters to improve the recognition rate
message:
added new filters to improve the recognition rate

The algorithm now uses custom edge detection + noise removal +
hough-line-transform do  align the image before applying
the detection mask.

Currently this script DOES NOT APPLY the mask or outputs the lmr
string. The mask needs to be adjusted to the input image size.
Previously the transformed image was of fixed size.

title: Choose a Point-functionality added
message:
Choose a Point-functionality added

By using a custom View class DragPointView, the user can choose and
move a Point on the image. The coordinates of the point are displayed.
The application is now locked in landscape mode.
still todo: make the user add exactly four points and connect them to
quadrangle. Pass the coordinates to the image manipulation section.

title: "Add Photo"-Application added
message:
"Add Photo"-Application added

-the empty android studio project with opencv included now allows the user
to either choose a photo from gallery or to take a new photo.
-the photo is then displayed in an image view and, if it was taken by the
user, stored as "ICT.jpg" in the primary external storage directory for
further usage.

title: Added filestructure for python scripts
message:
Added filestructure for python scripts
Added script for testing the opencv perspective transformation for quadrangle to quadrangle mapping
Moved canny_test.py script to the new python folder

the perspectiv_transf.py script can be used to test the quality of of the Transformation.
Useage: after starting the script select 4 points by clicking them with the mouse.
	To close the windows press 'ESC'
canny_test.py DEPENDS ON numpy and opencv.
	- numpy can be obtained via the python package
	  manager (pip)
	- opencv can be obtained from the official
	  website or by a package manager (python-opencv
	  on most distributions)

title: Added script for testing the opencv canny edge detector
message:
Added script for testing the opencv canny edge detector

the canny_test.py script can be used to test the
parametrization of the canny edge detector (threshold1,
threshold2).
canny_test.py DEPENDS ON numpy and opencv.
	- numpy can be obtained via the python package
	  manager (pip)
	- opencv can be obtained from the official
	  website or by a package manager (python-opencv
	  on most distributions)
